                                                            LOCATOR LOG

 THIS REPORT IS READ IN THE INCREASING MILEPOST DIRECTION FROM THE BOTTOM OF THE PAGE UP. THEREFORE, ALL THE HEADERS ARE AT
 THE BOTTOM OF THE PAGE.


 HEADER                                 DATA ELEMENT

 CITY                                   CITY NUMBER
 U/R                                    RURAL/URBAN CODE
 FNC                                    STATE FUNCTIONAL CLASSIFICATION
 SEQ                                    ACCIDENT SEQUENCE NUMBER
 SRMP                                   STATE ROUTE MILEPOST
 A/B                                    STATE ROUTE MILEPOST AHEAD BACK INDICATOR
 DIR                                    ROADWAY INVENTORY DIRECTION
 L/R IND                                ROADWAY LEFT RIGHT INDICATOR
 FEATURE                                LABEL
 LEFT SIDE READ UP                      ROADWAY DESCRIPTION
 CENTER READ UP                         ROADWAY DESCRIPTION
 RIGHT SIDE READ UP                     ROADWAY DESCRIPTION
 ARM                                    ACCUMULATED ROUTE MILE
 SIG                                    INTERSECTION TRAFFIC CONTROL TYPE
 CHN                                    ROADWAY CHANNELIZATION
 INT                                    CROSSROAD CONFIGURATION TYPE
 # LNS L R                              ROADWAY DECREASING NUMBER OF LANES / ROADWAY INCREASING NUMBER OF LANES
 CMPS DIRN                              ROADWAY COMPASS DIRECTION




























 FOR DESCRIPTION AND DEFINITION OF DATA ELEMENTS, REFER TO THE "TRIPS USER GUIDE" , "DATA ELEMENT DEFINITIONS".  FOR ACCIDENT DATA
 QUESTIONS OR INFORMATION, PLEASE CONTACT THE COLLISION DATA SECTION AT (360) 570-2454.  FOR REPORT PROBLEMS, QUESTIONS  RELATING TO
 THE TRIPS SYSTEM OR TO SCHEDULE TRIPS TRAINING, CONTACT TRIPS MAINTENANCE AND COORDINATION, (360) 570-2406.
